race.comment: Charge of the light brigade! Lots of very fast horses engaged but sticking with the unbeaten CHASING TIME (10) who scored this track and trip on debut over the winner then put away. The figure was good enough to account for these and returns fitter for two trials. Drawn well and can make it two from two. RUNAROUND SUE (12) is overdue for a win and looks a danger. Placed all three this time in over similar distances and very well weighted here with the claim. Tricky gate but expected to feature. DIAMANTINA ROSE (11) is going well, resuming with a maiden win by a space then finishing third last time. RUNAROUND SUE was just ahead go her that day. Tricky gate here but super consistent and can give a sight. TURN UP THE MUSIC (16) is rarely far away and best form is here. Has a low draw and can take a sit and charge late. HARD LANDING (3) was thereabouts latest and is well in here with the claim. Veteran sprinter who has won 2/3 at course and distance and will keep coming.
